    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It's a common go-lang thing, when there are return values like `ret1, ret2, ret2, err` -- if the `err` is non-nil, then all other return values are ignored. \r\nAll callers that call something which return error as the last retval should always check the error first. ",
